Sierra Village first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]] formed from part of the [[Mi-Wuk Village, California|Mi-Wuk Village CDP]] and additional area.<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Sierra Village had a population of 411. The population density was {{convert|159.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Sierra Village was 347 (84.4%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 6 (1.5%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 11 (2.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 5 (1.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 41 (10.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 27 persons (6.6%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Sierra Village CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0671834 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 194 households, out of which 44 (22.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 82 (42.3%) were married-couple households, 6 (3.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 52 (26.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 54 (27.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 59 households (30.4%) were one person, and 27 (13.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.12.<ref name=DP1/> There were 121 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (62.4% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Sierra Village CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0671834 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 68 people (16.5%) under the age of 18, 41 people (10.0%) aged 18 to 24, 91 people (22.1%) aged 25 to 44, 94 people (22.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 117 people (28.5%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 48.4{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 144.6 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 553 housing units at an average density of {{convert|215.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 194 (35.1%) were occupied. Of these, 134 (69.1%) were owner-occupied, and 60 (30.9%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

